messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /printshops/{id}/reviews

All HTTP methods acceptable?
- false

Per-method acceptability (based on code)
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation
- In ReviewController there is no class-level @RequestMapping, so no additional prefix is applied; the method-level @RequestMapping values are the full paths.
- The method addPrintShopReview is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/reviews", method = RequestMethod.POST) — this explicitly enables POST on /printshops/{id}/reviews.
- The method getPrintShopReviews is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/reviews", method = RequestMethod.GET) — this explicitly enables GET on the same path.
- No @RequestMapping in the code for that exact path declares HEAD, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, OPTIONS, TRACE or a wildcard that would allow all methods, so those are not considered acceptable based on the source.
